# SewerMenu

A feature-rich trainer for Schedule I built on MelonLoader.

## Requirements

- Schedule I (v0.4.2f9 or compatible)
- MelonLoader v0.7.1 or later

## Installation

1. Install MelonLoader on your Schedule I game
2. Download `SewerMenu.dll` from releases
3. Place the DLL in your `Schedule I/Mods` folder
4. Launch the game

## Controls

| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| F8 | Toggle menu |
| ESC | Close menu |

## Features

### Player

**God Mode** - Become invincible to all damage sources.

**Infinite Stamina** - Sprint and perform actions without stamina drain.

**Sprint Speed** - Multiply your movement speed from 1x to 10x with quick presets or fine-tuned slider control.

**Jump Height** - Adjust jump power from 1x to 10x for reaching otherwise inaccessible areas.

**NoClip** - Phase through walls, floors, and any solid geometry. Use WASD to move, Space/Ctrl for vertical movement.

**Fly Mode** - Free flight in any direction. Hold Shift for a speed boost. Adjustable base speed.

**Teleport System** - Save your current position with preset location names. Teleport back to any saved location instantly. Locations persist between sessions.

### Economy

**Cash Editor** - Set your cash to any amount or add funds incrementally. Preset buttons for common amounts from $1K to $1M.

**Bank Editor** - Modify your online bank balance. Supports amounts up to $10M+ with proper transaction handling.

**XP Editor** - Add experience points or set your tier directly. Jump to any rank instantly.

**Unlock All Products** - Immediately unlock every product in the game without meeting requirements.

**Free Purchases** - All shop purchases cost nothing while enabled.

### Items

**Item Spawner** - Browse and spawn any item in the game. Filter by category, select quantities from 1 to 999. Dedicated spawner window available for easier browsing.

**Stack Size Modifier** - Increase maximum stack sizes by 2x, 5x, 10x, 50x, or set all stacks to maximum capacity.

**Infinite Items** - Consumable items are not depleted when used.

**Quality Override** - Force all crafted items to a specific quality percentage.

**Instant Grow** - Immediately mature all planted crops. Optional auto-grow keeps plants at full growth continuously.

### World

**Time Control** - Set the time of day with a slider or use quick presets for morning, noon, evening, and midnight. Skip forward by hours or entire days.

**Police Management** - Disable police spawning entirely, clear your current wanted level, or remove all active police from the map.

**NPC Freeze** - Stop all NPC movement and AI. Useful for screenshots or avoiding interruptions.

**Unlock Properties** - Gain access to all purchasable properties without paying.

### Visuals

**ESP** - See entities through walls with customizable filters:
- NPCs
- Items
- Vehicles
- Police

Optional distance display shows how far each entity is. Adjustable maximum render distance from 10m to 500m.

**Freecam** - Detach the camera and fly freely through the world. Adjustable movement speed and look sensitivity. Teleport the camera back to your player position at any time.

**Debug Overlay** - Technical information display including:
- FPS counter
- Player position coordinates
- Player rotation
- Current velocity
- Game state information

### Settings

**Configuration** - All settings and saved teleport locations are automatically saved and persist between game sessions.

## User Interface

The menu features a tabbed interface for easy navigation between feature categories. Each feature includes:

- Clear toggle switches with on/off status indicators
- Sliders for adjustable values
- Preset buttons for quick value selection
- Informational displays showing current game values

The interface is designed to be usable without keyboard input for most operations, using button-based controls throughout.

## Notes

- Some features may behave differently in multiplayer contexts
- Saved locations are stored locally in the mod configuration
- The menu can be repositioned by dragging the title bar

## Troubleshooting

**Menu not appearing**
- Verify MelonLoader is installed correctly
- Check the MelonLoader console for error messages
- Ensure the DLL is in the correct Mods folder

**Features not working**
- Some features require being in-game (not in menus)
- Try toggling the feature off and on
- Check if the game version is compatible

## Disclaimer

This mod is intended for single-player use. Use responsibly.
